</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-44_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Raynaud's phenomenon, often referred to as Raynaud's, is a common vascular condition that affects blood circulation in extremities such as fingers, toes, ears, and more. When exposed to cold or emotional stress, individuals with Raynaud's experience extreme narrowing of their blood vessels, leading to a change in the colour of their skin. These colour changes typically progress from white to blue and eventually red. Raynaud's attacks can be painful, especially when blood circulation returns. The condition can also affect lips, nose, ears, and nipples.
