</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-53_">Primary Raynaud's is the most common form, occurring on its own without associated autoimmune or connective tissue diseases. It mainly affects women under the age of 30 and usually doesn't cause tissue damage.
