</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-119_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-120_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-121_">Key facts and statistics
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Winter_wellness_Coping_with_Raynaud_s_in_cold_weather_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708157438" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Winter_wellness_Coping_with_Raynaud_s_in_cold_weather_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708157438 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Winter_wellness_Coping_with_Raynaud_s_in_cold_weather_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708157438 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Winter_wellness_Coping_with_Raynaud_s_in_cold_weather_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708157438 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Winter_wellness_Coping_with_Raynaud_s_in_cold_weather_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708157438 320w" width="1741" height="1161" alt="Winter wellness Coping with Raynaud's in cold weather - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:9b0dbe41-cb28-4495-ae1e-9105a0d7d47f" title="Winter wellness: Coping with Raynaud's in cold weather - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-123_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-124_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-126_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-127_">Raynaud's affects up to 10 million people in the UK alone, making it a prevalent condition in society. It often presents before the age of 30 and is more common in women.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-129_">Primary Raynaud's is the most common form, occurring on its own without associated autoimmune or connective tissue diseases. It mainly affects women under the age of 30 and usually doesn't cause tissue damage.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-131_">Secondary Raynaud's is less common and is caused by underlying autoimmune conditions like scleroderma. It can lead to more serious complications, such as finger ulcers.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-133_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-134_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-135_">The effects of raynaud's
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Shining_a_light_on_Scleroderma_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708157966" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Shining_a_light_on_Scleroderma_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1708157966 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Shining_a_light_on_Scleroderma_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.png?v=1708157966 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Shining_a_light_on_Scleroderma_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1708157966 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Shining_a_light_on_Scleroderma_Awareness_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1708157966 320w" width="1638" height="1092" alt="Shining a light on Scleroderma Awareness - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -.png__PID:c72300e2-bab0-481e-9359-569fbcb19fb1" title="Shining a light on Scleroderma Awareness - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-137_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-138_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by FabrikaPhoto via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-140_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Raynaud's can significantly impact the daily lives of those affected. During an attack, the narrowing of blood vessels causes reduced blood flow and, subsequently, a lack of oxygen in affected areas. This can result in sensations like numbness, tingling, and a "pins-and-needles" feeling. Depending on the severity, some individuals may experience a loss of sensation or touch.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-142_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-143_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-144_">How to get involved
